  "title": "Construction supervisor",
  "description": "<p>Manages the construction portfolio through the implementation   phase and produces resource-loaded and leveled project schedules. Reviews   proposed designs to advise on constructability issues with adverse impacts.  </p>\n<p>Works with Supply Chain to identify and obtain resources (equipment, materials, and   contractors). Reviews contractors’ credentials in the established qualification process. Supports material receiving through inspection. Works   regularly with project managers, engineers, and planners to define   construction work package breakdown structure, requirements of work package   content, and priority of package development.    </p>\n<p>Develops   and executes multi-year strategy for efficiently executing construction   activities where multiple projects will be simultaneously occurring.  </p>\n<p>Leads an organization that develops project cost estimates, material and fabrication   requirements, and project completion dates, and evaluates engineering   estimates compared to construction control estimates.    </p>\n<p>Manages multiple progress reporting requirements depending on project type. </p>\n<p>Evaluates   work in progress to assure construction and installation of facilities and   equipment follow approved detailed design and engineering standards.         </p>\n<p>Conducts   productivity analysis to identify and resolve critical variances so projects   can achieve established objectives.             </p>\n<p>Maintains   accurate and current project documentation necessary to archive and close out   a project.     </p>\n<p>Develop   synergy contracting strategies for turnaround and construction efforts.                 </p>\n<p>Works to   implement appropriate turnaround best practices into the construction plan,   schedule, and execution of scheduled and emergency refinery outages.         </p>\n<p>Responsible   for overall adequate use of personnel to reduce equipment downtime, improve   efficiency, control costs, and anticipate further improvements.</p>",
